# TypeScript in this repository

## Default test stack

Use **Vitest** for unit and integration tests. See **`.cursor/rules/testing_ts.mdc`** for layout, `vi` mocks, and per-package `vitest.config.ts`.

## Typing and correctness

- **`strict`** TypeScript in each workspace’s `tsconfig.json`. No `@ts-ignore` unless unavoidable and documented.
- Prefer **`neverthrow`** **`Result`** / **`ResultAsync`** for expected failures at **`lib/`**, **`services/`**, and gRPC client boundaries — not throws for validation or I/O control flow.
- **Zod v4** for runtime schemas; derive types with **`z.infer<typeof SomeSchema>`** — no parallel `interface` for the same shape.
- Workspace-specific compiler and style detail: **`frontend/.cursor/rules/typescript.mdc`**, **`aspire.svc/.cursor/rules/typescript.mdc`**.

## Input validation (mandatory)

- **All input** at trust boundaries (route handlers, server actions, gRPC client calls, env, external APIs, AI tool I/O, user JSON) **must** be validated against a **known schema** before domain logic runs.
- **Schema in its own module** — e.g. `validation/schemas.ts`, `lib/<feature>/*-schema.ts`, or `*-schema.ts` next to the boundary. Do not embed ad hoc shape checks in components, handlers, or repositories.
- **Validation in its own module** — e.g. `validation/assert-valid.ts`, `lib/validation/zod-result.ts`, or dedicated `validate*` helpers; call once at ingress and pass inferred types inward.
- **Zod only** for runtime validation in TypeScript (`safeParse` / project helpers). Types come from **`z.infer`**, not duplicate hand-written interfaces for the same payload.
- Prefer **`safeParse`** and **`Result`** in request paths; **`parse`** only for fail-fast boot env (see **`frontend/.cursor/rules/validation.mdc`** / **`aspire.svc/.cursor/rules/validation.mdc`** for boundaries and naming).
- Map failures to structured errors at the edge — not raw Zod dumps to users (see **`.cursor/rules/error.mdc`**).

## Style and lint

- Match **ESLint** / **Prettier** and naming in the nearest workspace (`frontend/`, `aspire.svc/`, `*.svc/client`).
- No **`any`**; no **`z.any()`**. Use **`unknown`** + narrowing or explicit schemas.
- Do not put Zod schemas inside **`components/ui/`** or presentational components — keep them in **`lib/`**, **`services/`**, or route-adjacent modules.
